      "text": "I turned your beats into a tight 5-shot storyboard with a clean deadpan build and a warmer final push-in.\n\nWhat’s working in this version:\n- **Shot 1** establishes the whole joke immediately in one readable frame.\n- **Shot 2** gives the pause the scene needs so the comedy can breathe.\n- **Shot 3** sharpens the setup by isolating the doctor’s question.\n- **Shot 4** lets the panda’s desperation spike just enough.\n- **Shot 5** gives the punchline a subtle emotional weight instead of playing it broad.\n\nOne thing I’d keep an eye on: you call him **psychiatrist** in the shot description but **psychologist/doctor** elsewhere. For consistency, I’d treat him as a **psychologist** unless you specifically want a more medical read.\n\nThe next practical move is to generate the storyboard board and check whether the framing rhythm really lands visually before we lock keyframes."
