      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "Done — I wrote the full sidecar prompts for all 10 keyframes, keeping the visual language minimal, deadpan, and consistent with the approved storyboard.\n\nThe prompts are tuned to:\n- keep the **therapy room clean and uncluttered**\n- preserve **character continuity** from the approved sheets\n- avoid broad or cartoony comedy\n- use **small performance shifts** between start and end frames\n- follow the **storyboard panel for each shot** as the upstream visual reference\n\nPerformance shape across the set:\n- **Shot 1:** setup to confession landing\n- **Shot 2:** held reaction with the mug beat\n- **Shot 3:** calm question, almost no movement\n- **Shot 4:** the panda’s one real emotional spike\n- **Shot 5:** notes → glasses adjustment → warm final insight\n\nAt this point, the keyframe prompt package is ready for image generation. You’ll need to run the keyframe generation step and review the 10 PNGs before we treat those shot anchors as locked."
