      "id": "assistant-1774458391989-hevwfo",
      "role": "assistant",
      "text": "Drafted — the 5-shot sequence now has full planning entries with durations, keyframe anchors, and transition logic.\n\n### Timing pass\n- **SHOT-01 — 6s**  \n  Gives the setup and long first line enough room to breathe.\n\n- **SHOT-02 — 4s**  \n  Short reaction beat for the mug sip and set-down.\n\n- **SHOT-03 — 4s**  \n  Clean question beat, minimal movement.\n\n- **SHOT-04 — 4s**  \n  Enough space for the panda’s emotional spike.\n\n- **SHOT-05 — 5s**  \n  Slightly longer to support the slow push-in and the final line landing warmly.\n\n### Transition logic\n- **SHOT-01:** opening\n- **SHOT-02:** scene-change from the wide setup to the psychologist reaction shot\n- **SHOT-03:** continuity from the psychologist reaction into the tighter question close-up\n- **SHOT-04:** scene-change to the panda response close-up\n- **SHOT-05:** scene-change back to the psychologist for the closing insight\n\nThis gives the scene a nice rhythm: establish, pause, question, burst, resolution.\n\nOne important note: in the actual workflow, **keyframe review is still technically the upstream gate** before motion is fully locked. But since you asked to proceed on the assumption that the storyboard is approved, the shot plan itself is now in place and ready to build prompts from."
